  "body": "In Section 7 \"Contract Creation\" and in Section 8 \"Message Call\", the refunded gas is defined differently, especially after exceptional halting.\r\n\r\nIn Section 7, `g'` is defined in terms of `g**` and the returned global state (indicating if the halting was normal or exceptional.)  However, in Section 8, `g'` is directly taken from the return value of `Îž`.  I think Section 8 should do the same as Section 7.\r\n\r\nI need to check the clients' behaviors, but I'm sure all clients agree because this is a frequent case.\r\n\r\nThis has to be fixed before #232.  Otherwise the gas-refunding nature of \"REVERT\" cannot be expressed.",
